env PAGER=cat man timing_path_based_enable_exhaustive_depth_bounde d_by_gba
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_path_ba...bounded_by_gba(25.10)  timing_path_ba...bounded_by_gba(25.10)

Name
       timing_path_based_enable_exhaustive_depth_bounded_by_gba

Syntax
       timing_path_based_enable_exhaustive_depth_bounded_by_gba

       {true | false}

       Default: true

       Enables the timing report to bound PBA results by GBA slacks of the re-
       spective  leftover  nworst paths, whenever exhaustive depth for an end-
       point is exhausted.

       When set to true, during exhaustive  PBA,  if  you  specify  exhaustive
       depth  as  N, and an endpoint has nworst paths greater than N, then the
       timing report will show the worst path corresponding to worst slack out
       of worst PBA slack (out of first  N  paths)  and  GBA  slack  (for  the
       (N+1)th  path). Here, the variable N refers to exhaustive PBA depth and
       can be set  using  the  timing_pba_exhaustive_path_nworst_limit  global
       variable.

       When  set  to  false,  during exhaustive PBA, if you specify exhaustive
       depth as N, and an endpoint has nworst paths greater than N,  then  the
       software will ignore the paths with depth greater than N, which may re-
       sult in reporting an optimistic PBA slack for the endpoint reaching the
       depth.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

